      <unitdate normal="1943/1968" type="inclusive">Inclusive: 1943-1968; Bulk: 1947-1954</unitdate>
      <abstract>Mr. W. Whittier Wright is a Vanderbilt Alumnus who graduated in 1943. His collection consists of correspondence between himself and Agrarian
        literary writer Andrew Nelson Lytle.</abstract>
    </did>
    <bioghist>
      <head>Biographical/Historical Note</head>
      <p>1941-1943 Attended Vanderbilt University, Nashville, Tennessee</p>
      <p>1943 Received B.A. from Vanderbilt University</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent>
      <head>Scope And Content Note</head>
      <p>The W. Whittier Wright Collection was a generous donation given to Special Collections by Mr. Wright in 1998. W. Whittier Wright is a graduate of Vanderbilt University, whose correspondence with Mr. Andrew Nelson Lytle began while Mr. Wright
        attended the University in the forties. The collection is contained in one half-sized Hollinger box.</p>
        <p>The correspondence includes incoming and outgoing letters, spanning the years 1946 to 1968. The series is subdivided into Outgoing and Incoming Correspondence. Mr. Wright states in a letter to Vanderbilt University Special Collections that
          the correspondence shared between the two &#8220;speaks more to anecdotes of our friendship than it does to Lytle!&#8217;s writings...&#8221;</p>
    </scopecontent>
